Tripe and Trotters (Pens en Pootjies) By Patience Watlington  Ingredients 1 kg tripe, cleaned 1 ox trotter, cleaned Salt and pepper 5 Bay leaves 2.5 ml cooking oil 1 large onion Curry and borrie powder 500 g beans of choice, cooked  Method Rinse tripe and trotter well. Cook with salt and bay leaves until soft. Cut tripe into bite sized pieces and set aside Heat the oil in a pot and saut√© onions. Add curry and borrie. Add tripe and trotters and simmer through for approximately 15 minutes. Add cooked beans and some of the stock from cooked tripe and trotter.